CatDescriptText: Arlene Palmore, 3424 Webster Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 25, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Do you think there would be less juvenile delinquency if the father were restored to his original role as sole head of the house?" answer reads: "Yes, I do believe that if the father were restored as head of the house, it would be better."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Arlene Palmore wearing six pocket button down tweed suit jacket and round decorative metal earrings, standing in interior with seated woman wearing eyeglasses, dark coat, and light colored patterned head scarf on left and rack of hanging dresses on right
